  <header>
    <h1>Ways to Connect Ryanair Customer Service: By Phone and Email | A Detailed Guide</h1>
  </header>

  <section>
    <p>
      Ryanair's main customer service number is <strong>1-800-Ryanair</strong> (<strong>+1-808-751-2262</strong> or <strong>+44-203-900-3009</strong>) for the US and UK. Live support is available <strong>24/7</strong>. This guide explains how to reach Ryanair customer service through phone, live chat, email, and other channels—with tips to reduce wait times.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why Contact a Live Person at Ryanair?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Flight changes or cancellations:</strong> Get assistance modifying or canceling your booking.</li>
      <li><strong>Booking clarification:</strong> Help with understanding your reservation details.</li>
      <li><strong>Refunds and compensation:</strong> Speak with a live agent for complex refund cases.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical glitches:</strong> Quickly resolve issues with booking or payment.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact Options</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> Call <strong>+1-808-751-2262</strong> or <strong>+44-203-900-3009</strong> and press “0” or say “agent” to speak with a representative.</li>
      <li><strong>Live Chat:</strong> Visit Ryanair’s official website Help section and use the live chat feature.</li>
      <li><strong>Social Media:</strong> Message Ryanair on Twitter or Facebook for prompt responses.</li>
      <li><strong>Mobile App:</strong> Use the app to chat or call support directly from your phone.</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> Ideal for less urgent queries and record-keeping.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Step-by-Step: Talking to a Live Person</h2>
    <p>
      To connect with a live Ryanair agent:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Call <strong>+1-808-751-2262</strong> or <strong>+44-203-900-3009</strong>.</li>
      <li>Follow the prompts and select the most relevant option.</li>
      <li>For faster connection, press “0” or say “agent.”</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
